Researchers here at Bounce Energy Labs have discovered a new kind of renewable energy that can be transported without the use of powerlines! 

The energy is transmitted from the powerplant to the factory through the air and bounces off of mirrors to change direction along carefully designed Power Paths.

A hurricane recently came through our test site and rotated all of our mirrors into the wrong position. The employee who designed the Power Paths left a couple of months ago and took all of his maps of the Power Paths with him. (What a jerk!)

We don't really have time to sit down and figure this out. Can you give us a hand? 
(We don't have any money to pay you, but you can consider it an unpaid internship.)

Goal: Shoot the energy ball from the powerplant and bounce it off the mirrors into the factory in as few actions as possible.

Arrows will show you where the energy will leave and where the factory can accept the energy.

Click the mirror to rotate it clockwise. Click SHOOT below to release the energy ball.
Right-click to rotate the mirror clockwise.

Each level starts at 1000pts and you lose pts for each of the following actions:

Mirror Adjustment: -10pts
Attempt (Ball Shot): -50pts
Reset Level: -50pts
Solution Bounces: -25pts per bounce (only bounces from the final attempt count and are calculated at the end of the level)
